Chief Magistrate Court sitting in Ado-Ekiti has sentenced one Ali Haruna to two years imprisonment for taking his cows for grazing in a farmland in Ado-Ekiti and destroying crops. September 19, 2016 In "News" A sixty five-year-old man, Yahaya Bankole, was on Thursday charged with stealing rams and cows valued at N830,000 in an Ojo Magistrates’ Court, Lagos. Bankole, who is a trader at Alaba Rago Market, Lagos is facing a count charge of theft. February 19, 2015 In "News" A 25 year-old-man, Ekene Nwanne, was on Thursday sentenced to 14 years imprisonment by an Egor Magistrates’ Court sitting in Benin for attempting to use a minor for ritual. September 28, 2017 In "Crime Alert"